{{Italic title}} {{Infobox artwork | image_file = SahagianAcquaGrylli2001.jpg | painting_alignment = | image_size = 200px | title = Acqua Grylli | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = Beth Sahagian | year = 2001 | type = bronze | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter__metric = | diameter_imperial = | imperial_unit = in | metric_unit = cm | city = Milwaukee, Wisconsin | museum = | coordinates = | owner = Milwaukee Riverwalk }}
'''''Acqua Grylli''''' is a [[public art]] work by [[United States|American]] artist [[Beth Sahagian]], located on the [[Milwaukee Riverwalk|Riverwalk]] in downtown [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]].<ref name=OMC>{{cite web|last=Sherman|first=Jeff|title=Milwaukee Buzz August 2001|url=http://staff.onmilwaukee.com/buzz/articles/augustbuzz01.html|work=OnMilwaukee.com|accessdate=13 December 2011}}</ref> The artwork is a bronze arch depicting a mythical female figure. It is located on the west side of the Milwaukee River between Wells Street and Kilbourn Avenue.
The work was commissioned by the Riverwalk [[business improvement district]] and dedicated in August 2001.<ref name=OMC /> The figure is imagined as a guardian or gatekeeper.<ref name=Bookcrossing>{{cite web|last=aimlesst|title=Creating a Buzz on the Milwaukee Riverwalk |url=http://www.bookcrossing.com/articles/1848|work=BookCrossing.com|accessdate=13 December 2011}}</ref>
Sahagian is a Milwaukee artist and proprietor of Vanguard Sculpture Services.<ref name=Vanguard>{{cite web|title=Vanguard |url=http://www.vanguardsculptureservices.com/|work=vanguardsculptureservices.com|accessdate=13 December 2011}}</ref>
